<item>
            <title>[CXF-2135] JAXB binding files with no schemaLocation don&apos;t work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2135</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In order to clean up other code and prevent other bugs, I am breaking the code that allows JAXB binding files with no schemaLocation attribute to work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 2.2 and earlier, this worked because we fed all the schemas to JAXB under the same key. This is contrary to the doc and likely to cause other more confusing problems, such as mis-applied customizations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct solution seems to be to just leave off the schemaLocation, but as of JAXB 2.1.10, that doesn&apos;t work, since JAXB doesn&apos;t handle this case for outboard customization files. Heck, perhaps recycling outboard customization files with JAXB is just not a good idea, period.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
